Package com.barbablanka.henry.mmsreflect

Class Reflector

java.lang.Object
com.barbablanka.henry.mmsreflect.Reflector
public class Reflector extends Object
Reflection tool

This is a utility class and therefor should never be instanced!

Be careful upon editing this file as you may break classes using it!

This file contains a lot of small utilities' method to extract set and uses class, methods and fields from private files.

All methods in this file automatically catch errors and print stackTrace when using it, be sure to check your console for any errors.

You cannot instantiate constructor using this file and you will need to instantiate them in their respective file due to autoboxing.
It could be possible to instantiate constructor taking only object as arguments, but almost all of them take primitive types making it impossible to extract.

Take a look at the provided link for autoboxing explanation.

Author:
Florian Chanson
See Also:
  • https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/data/autoboxing.html

  • Method Details

    • getClass

      public static Class<?> getClass(String path)
      Extract a class from a java package

      Extract the class using the class package declaration + name
      (e.g: com.google.android.mms.pdu.PduPart)

      The found class will be returned as a class capture or null if the file doesn't exist

      Parameters:
      path - the class path
      Returns:
      a capture of the class or null if not found

    • invokeMethod

      public static <T> T invokeMethod(Method method, Object object, Class<T> type, Object... args)
      Invoke a method and return its data

      Invoke a method from a previously extracted class and return the method data.

      WARNING upon using this method with primitive types you must use their class version e.g:
      int.class -> Integer.class
      boolean.class -> Boolean.class
      float.class -> Float.class
      ...

      Or you will get a cast error due to autoboxing.
      Take a look at the provided link for autoboxing explanation.

      Type Parameters:
      T - a template parameter allowing us to use this one method to return anything
      Parameters:
      method - the method that must be invoked
      object - the class object instance or null if the method is static
      type - the type of data returned by the method
      args - the method args
      Returns:
      the data provided by the invoked method
      See Also:
      • https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/data/autoboxing.html

        For method that return nothing (void)
      • invokeMethod(Method, Object, Object...)

    • getMethod

      public static Method getMethod(Class<?> classData, String methodName, Class<?>... args)
      Extract a method

      Get a method from any previously extracted classes.
      The method is ready to run once extracted.

      You can also extract private/protected method.

      Parameters:
      classData - the class containing the desired method
      methodName - the method name
      args - the method args
      Returns:
      the method ready to be invoked or null if not found

    • setField

      public static void setField(Object edit, String fieldName, Object value)
      Set field value

      Allow you to manually set any class field value.

      In many classes is much safer to use class setter to do that, but if they are missing, or you need to update one specific value this is the method you need.

      With this method you can also access and set private/protected fields.

      Parameters:
      edit - the object containing the field or null if the field is static
      fieldName - the name of the field that must be edited
      value - the value you want to put in the field

    • getObject

      public static <T> T getObject(Class<?> classData, String fieldName, Object object, Class<T> type)
      Extract objet field from classes

      Warning you cannot extract primitive types using this method due to autoboxing.

      Take a look at the provided link for autoboxing explanation.

      Type Parameters:
      T - template object allowing us to return any type of object with only one function
      Parameters:
      classData - the class containing the desired object
      fieldName - the extracted field name
      object - the class object instance or null if the field is static
      type - the type of class expected to be returned
      Returns:
      the field value or null if not found
      See Also:
      • https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/data/autoboxing.html

        Use the appropriate method for each primitive:
      • getInteger(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
      • getIntegerArray(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
      • getBoolean(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
      • getBooleanArray(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
      • getFloat(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
      • getFloatArray(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
      • getDouble(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
      • getDoubleArray(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
      • getLong(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
      • getLongArray(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
      • getShort(java.lang.Class<?>, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object)
